<@805905681324441601>  going back to what we were talking about above, liquidity mgmt on Orca/Solana...

Was just looking more into Orca and chatting with someone from the team.

I learned that 

1) team treasury is currently sitting on $6M worth of liquidity tokens and this is increasing every day. This is generated from the .05% protocol fee on pools 

2) all of this liquidity is in constant product pools

3) their concentrated pools which they recently introduced and call "Whirlpools" are already generating ~40M daily volume on ~25M TVL. The largest pool (SOL/USDC) is generating ~10M daily volume on ~6M TVL

4) The reason the treasury is not shifting its liquidity to Whirlpools (concentrated pools), in the words of the team: "The current issue is Whirlpools demand more active management"

So... I think there could be real opportunity here. As much of an ETH maxi as I usually am, the Orca growth metrics are massive and it seems they could really use something like Gamma
